The paper deals with online learning algorithms and their regret bounds, which are typically studied in the machine learning subfield of computer science (cs.LG). The problem of online local learning involves selecting labels for pairs of items, which can be seen as a graph problem, suggesting the category of computer science dealing with graphs and networks (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of semi-definite programming, which is a technique commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and optimization (cs.CC). The paper's focus on achieving optimal regret bounds suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), which often deals with optimizing performance metrics.
